    </div>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_rating", slug: "freezer-storage" %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How to Use the Freezer Storage Time Calculator</h2>
      <p>
        Select a food category and then choose the specific food item. The calculator instantly displays the recommended maximum freezer storage time for optimal quality, along with storage tips specific to that food. These recommendations are based on USDA and FDA guidelines and assume your freezer maintains a constant temperature of 0 degrees F (-18 degrees C).
      </p>
      <p>
        Proper freezing is one of the most effective ways to reduce food waste and save money. Understanding how long different foods maintain their quality in the freezer helps you plan grocery shopping, meal prep, and food rotation. Foods stored beyond the recommended time remain safe to eat but may suffer from freezer burn, texture changes, or flavor degradation.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>Understanding Freezer Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Frozen food is safe indefinitely at 0 degrees F because freezing prevents the growth of microorganisms that cause spoilage and foodborne illness. However, quality degrades over time due to freezer burn (surface dehydration caused by air exposure), ice crystal formation (which damages cell structure), and oxidation (which causes off-flavors, especially in fatty foods). The recommended storage times balance safety with quality.
      </p>

      <h3>Packaging for the Freezer</h3>
      <p>
        The single most important factor in freezer storage quality is packaging. Vacuum sealing removes virtually all air and can extend freezer life by 2-3 times compared to regular freezer bags. Heavy-duty aluminum foil, freezer paper, and press-and-seal bags are also effective. Standard plastic wrap and regular zip-top bags provide inadequate protection for long-term storage.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How long can you freeze meat?</h3>
      <p>Steaks and roasts last up to 12 months; ground meat 3-4 months. Vacuum sealing extends these times significantly.</p>

      <h3>Is food safe after the recommended freezer time?</h3>
      <p>Yes, frozen food remains safe indefinitely at 0 degrees F. Recommended times are for quality, not safety.</p>

      <h3>What temperature should a freezer be?</h3>
      <p>0 degrees F (-18 degrees C) or below. Use a freezer thermometer to verify.</p>

      <h3>How do I prevent freezer burn?</h3>
      <p>Remove as much air as possible. Use vacuum sealers, press-and-seal bags, or double wrapping.</p>

      <h3>Can you refreeze thawed food?</h3>
      <p>Food thawed in the refrigerator can be refrozen within 1-2 days. Food thawed by other methods should be cooked first.</p>
    </article>

